Date: 0/9/1913
Source: NZ Farmer
Author:
Vol / Page: 1158
Edition:
Quote: This condition has acuired the name of 'Waihi disease' on account of the fact that the first-noted cases occurred in the districts of Waihi, North Taranaki. There is good reason to believe that Waihi disease is allied to osteo-malacia. In the case of Waihi disease the condition had arisen as a result of the depletion of the soil of its nutritive elements. Rib bones, showing bulbous-like enlargements characteristic of Waihi disease, which attacks dairy cattle grazing upon certain kinds of second-class light land.
