Author:
Vol / Page: 12/304
Edition:
Quote: There are, however, certain areas in which a decided malnutrition disease develops in stock, mostly in dairy cattle, in which the deficiency is phosphoric acid, since the symptoms are those of `Waihi disease', a bone-malnutrition trouble manifested by lameness, swollen joints, and curable by dosing the subjects with phosphates as a lick or medicinal drench ...
